>
  <article class="prose-dolphin max-w-none">

    <div id="ai-summary" class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-6 not-prose mb-8">
      <p class="text-base italic text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>AI Summary:</strong> Dolphin Centrifuge supplies the DMB-062 — Dolphin's highest-capacity manual-clean disc stack centrifuge clarifier. The DMB-062 processes approximately 62 GPM of diesel-viscosity fluid (92 GPM rated on water). Applications include major turbine lube oil purification (30,000+ HP systems), bulk diesel and gas oil polishing at 62–81 GPM, large marine engine lube systems, and centralized lube oil purification for large industrial complexes. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of experience in centrifugal separation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="specs">DMB-062 Specifications</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Parameter</th>
            <th>Value</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Separation type</td><td>Two-phase clarifier (liquid-liquid or liquid-solid)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Diesel throughput</td><td>~62 GPM (13 cSt at operating temperature)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Rated throughput (water)</td><td>~92 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cleaning method</td><td>Manual (bowl disassembly required for solids removal)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bowl construction</td><td>Carbon steel standard</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Power supply</td><td>460V / 3-phase / 60 Hz standard (other voltages available)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">Throughput figures are for typical fluids at listed conditions. Actual capacity varies with feed viscosity, temperature, density difference, and solids loading. Contact Dolphin Centrifuge for application-specific confirmation.</p>

    <h2 id="capacity">DMB-062 Capacity by Application (GPM)</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Application / Fluid</th>
            <th>Throughput (GPM)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Gas oil at 40&deg;C</td><td>~81 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Diesel fuel (13 cSt)</td><td>~62 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lube oil (R&amp;O)</td><td>~33 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lube oil (detergent)</td><td>~28 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Steam turbine oil</td><td>~60 GPM</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2>The Case for High-Capacity Manual-Clean</h2>
    <p>
      For applications with clean, low-solids fluid — such as turbine lube oil purification or clean diesel polishing — a manual-clean centrifuge at high throughput often provides better economics than a self-cleaning unit. The DMB-062 delivers 62 GPM diesel throughput without the complexity, control system cost, and maintenance overhead of hydraulic self-cleaning mechanisms.
    </p>
    <p>
      In large turbine lube oil applications, fluid cleanliness is usually high (low particulate loading), and cleaning intervals are long — measured in weeks or months rather than days. A single DMB-062 on a planned cleaning schedule outperforms multiple smaller self-cleaning units from both cost and simplicity perspectives. Dolphin Centrifuge can help you calculate the optimal cleaning interval based on your fluid analysis.
    </p>

    <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
    <div class="not-prose my-10 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold bg-gold/10 p-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="text-navy font-bold text-lg mb-1">Specifying the DMB-062 for a major turbine installation?</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Our engineers can calculate your optimal cleaning interval, confirm sizing, and quote the right configuration for your power plant, marine, or industrial facility.</p>
      </div>
