        Request a Quote &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 id="applications">Key Applications</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10 not-prose">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Major Power Generation Turbines</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Power station steam turbines and gas turbines above 30,000 HP with large lube oil reservoirs. The DMB-062 provides continuous bypass purification at 33–60 GPM on turbine oil, maintaining ISO cleanliness targets across very large oil reservoirs that smaller units cannot service efficiently.</p>
        <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-navy hover:text-gold transition-colors">Lube Oil Centrifuge Details &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Bulk Diesel &amp; Gas Oil Polishing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Large fuel depots, tank farms, and bulk storage terminals requiring high-throughput diesel and gas oil polishing. The DMB-062 processes 62–81 GPM continuously, maintaining fuel quality across large storage volumes and keeping water and particulates at acceptable levels for downstream equipment.</p>
        <a href="/diesel-centrifuge/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-navy hover:text-gold transition-colors">Diesel Centrifuge Details &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Large Marine Lube Oil Systems</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Large marine vessels with multiple propulsion turbines, main engine lube systems, and auxiliary machinery lube oil requiring centralized purification. The DMB-062 handles marine application conditions including variable pitch, shock loading, and the need for robust, reliable design.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Centralized Industrial Lube Systems</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Large industrial complexes, refineries, and chemical plants with centralized lubrication systems serving multiple large machines from a common reservoir. The DMB-062 handles the high throughput required for centralized purification of very large shared lube oil inventories.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the throughput of the DMB-062?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMB-062 processes ~62 GPM of diesel, ~81 GPM of gas oil at 40&deg;C, ~33 GPM of lube oil (R&amp;O), and ~60 GPM of steam turbine oil. Rated at 92 GPM on water-viscosity fluid — Dolphin&rsquo;s highest-capacity manual-clean model.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What turbine or system size is the DMB-062 suited for?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        At 33 GPM on lube oil (R&amp;O), the DMB-062 suits major turbines above 30,000 HP, large marine turbine installations, centralized <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/">lube oil</a> systems for multiple large turbines, and large petrochemical compressor trains with reservoirs of 15,000–50,000+ gallons.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What applications is the DMB-062 best suited for?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Major turbine lube oil (30,000+ HP), bulk diesel and gas oil polishing at 62–81 GPM, large marine lube systems, centralized lube oil purification for large industrial complexes, and offshore facilities requiring maximum throughput in a manual-clean design.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">Why choose manual-clean DMB-062 over a self-cleaning centrifuge?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        For clean <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/">turbine lube oil</a> with very low solids loading, the DMB-062 provides lower capital cost, no self-cleaning control complexity, and simpler maintenance than a self-cleaning unit. In large turbine systems, cleaning intervals of weeks or months make manual cleaning economically attractive. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> to calculate your specific cleaning interval.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">How does the DMB-062 compare to the DMPX-070?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMB-062 (62 GPM diesel, manual-clean) and <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-070/">DMPX-070</a> (59–72 GPM diesel, self-cleaning) have similar diesel throughput. The DMB-062 is lower cost and simpler for clean turbine lube oil with long cleaning intervals. The DMPX-070 is better for <a href="/waste-oil-centrifuge/">waste oil</a>, HFO, or crude oil processing where continuous automated desludging is essential.
      </p>
    </details>

